Visualization: Case 1- Optimize Treatment Costs for Self-Pay and Private Insurance Patients 5


Positive Insight:

Self-pay patients represent the highest proportion of unchanged cases (36 out of 138). This highlights an opportunity to improve cost-efficiency by focusing on better treatment outcomes with fewer resources.





Negative Insight:

Private insurance patients have the highest deterioration rate (37 out of 120 cases). This contributes to increased readmission costs, requiring targeted interventions to reduce deterioration and improve outcomes.




Case 1 ROI:
Cost-efficient treatment plans targeting self-pay and private insurance patients could save $11.2 million annually, with a 220% ROI. Improving recovery outcomes and reducing deterioration can boost both clinical outcomes and financial savings.
